A medical practitioner awaits for a patient to test for COVID-19 in Alexandra township, residents gathered to be screened and tested for coronavirus, the campaign is targeting Johannesburg epicenter. JOHANNESBURG - Government can no longer force anyone into state quarantine. The High Court in Pretoria has ruled that people who can self-isolate at home must be allowed to do so. READ: Level 3 and Level 4 regulations declared unconstitutional But if quarantine is broken, they can then be forced into a state facility. WATCH: People in quarantine refused tests The case was brought by rights group AfriForum, against Cooperative Governance Minister, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. It's another defeat for lockdown regulations set out by the National Coronavirus Command Council. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.